message.content: Most women in France have a relatively positive view of divorce. They consider it as a viable option to end an unhappy or dysfunctional marriage. Women in France generally believe that divorce provides them with the opportunity to pursue personal happiness and independence. They often view divorce as a means to escape from abusive or unfulfilling relationships, and they prioritize their own well-being and self-fulfillment. Additionally, French women tend to have a pragmatic approach towards divorce, focusing on the practical aspects such as financial stability and child custody arrangements. Overall, divorce is seen as a socially acceptable and empowering choice for women in France.
